SECTION 11: SPECIALIST DOMAIN KEYWORDS
================================================================================

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
11.1 CLOUD & INFRASTRUCTURE (IaC)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
KEYWORD           | MEANING
------------------|--------------------------------------
"Provision"       | Create cloud resources
"Drift"           | Real setup doesn't match code
"Cold Start"      | Serverless function wake-up delay
"Region-agnostic" | Works in any AWS/Azure region
"Infrastructure as Code" | Define infra in files
"Teardown"        | Delete/destroy resources
"State file"      | Terraform's record of what exists


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
11.2 AI ENGINEERING
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
KEYWORD           | MEANING
------------------|--------------------------------------
"RAG"             | Retrieval-Augmented Generation
"Embeddings"      | Vector representations of text
"Inference"       | Model running/thinking
"Token Limit"     | Maximum input/output size
"Fine-tuning"     | Training model on custom data
"Prompt injection"| Security attack via malicious prompts
"Hallucination"   | Model making things up
"Context window"  | How much text model can "see"
"Temperature"     | Randomness/creativity setting


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
11.3 CODE METRICS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"CYCLOMATIC COMPLEXITY" - Score of how many "paths" in code. Lower = better.
"COGNITIVE COMPLEXITY" - Score of how hard code is for HUMAN to understand.
"CODE SMELL" - Patterns indicating bad design (Long Method, God Class, etc.)


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
11.4 EVENT HANDLING
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"DEBOUNCE" - Wait for user to STOP doing something before acting.
"THROTTLE" - Only allow this action once every X seconds.
"EXPONENTIAL BACKOFF" - If server fails, wait 1s, then 2s, then 4s, then 8s...


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
11.5 DATABASE INTERNALS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
KEYWORD           | MEANING
------------------|--------------------------------------
"Indexing"        | Speed up queries
"Sharding"        | Split DB across servers
"ACID Compliance" | Data validity guarantee
"Deadlock"        | Two queries waiting for each other
"Connection Pool" | Reuse DB connections
"Query Plan"      | How DB executes a query
"Denormalization" | Flatten for read speed


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
11.6 SRE & RELIABILITY
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"INSTRUMENT" - Add code that measures HOW the code is running.
"CIRCUIT BREAKER" - Pattern that stops calling a broken service repeatedly.
"FUZZING" - Testing by throwing random garbage data at code.
"TELEMETRY" - The logs/metrics/traces your app sends out for monitoring.

OTHER SRE KEYWORDS:
- "SLO/SLA/SLI" - Service Level Objective/Agreement/Indicator
- "Runbook" - Step-by-step guide for handling incidents
- "Postmortem" - Analysis after an incident
- "Canary deploy" - Release to small % of users first
- "Blue-green" - Two identical environments, switch between them


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
11.7 CONCURRENCY & THREADING
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"MUTEX" - Lock that stops two threads from writing to same variable.
"DEADLOCK" - Two processes waiting for each other forever.
"NON-BLOCKING" - Code doesn't freeze while waiting for data.
"Thread-safe" - Safe to use from multiple threads.
"Semaphore" - Like mutex but allows N threads.
"Race condition" - Bug when timing causes unexpected results.


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
11.8 CRYPTOGRAPHY & AUTH
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
KEYWORD           | MEANING
------------------|--------------------------------------
"Salt"            | Random data added before hashing
"Hash"            | One-way transformation
"JWT"             | JSON Web Token for auth
"Symmetric"       | Same key encrypts/decrypts
"Asymmetric"      | Public/private key pair
"HMAC"            | Hash-based message authentication
"OAuth"           | Authorization framework
"CORS"            | Cross-Origin Resource Sharing


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
11.9 DATA ENGINEERING
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
KEYWORD           | MEANING
------------------|--------------------------------------
"ETL"             | Extract, Transform, Load
"Upsert"          | Update if exists, else insert
"Pivot"           | Reshape data (rows to columns)
"Batch Processing"| Handle data in chunks
"Schema"          | Data structure definition
"Normalized"      | Proper database structure
"Denormalized"    | Flattened for speed
"Seed"            | Reproducible random data


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
11.10 FRONTEND & WEB
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
KEYWORD          | MEANING
-----------------|--------------------------------------
"Responsive"     | Works on mobile and desktop
"Mobile-first"   | Design for phones first
"Pixel-perfect"  | Exact match to design
"Dark Mode"      | Support light/dark themes
"A11y"           | Accessibility (screen readers)
"Polyfill"       | Support old browsers
"Minified"       | Compressed for production


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
11.11 GIT & COLLABORATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
KEYWORD                | OUTPUT
-----------------------|---------------------------
"Conventional Commits" | Standardized messages (feat:, fix:, chore:)
"Changelog"            | Version history
