SECTION 13: META-PROMPTING (ADVANCED AI CONTROL)
================================================================================

KEYWORD: "TREE OF THOUGHTS"
AI explores multiple solutions before choosing best one.

KEYWORD: "DO NOT HALLUCINATE"
Explicitly warns AI not to invent fake libraries or methods.

KEYWORD: "CHAIN OF VERIFICATION"
AI double-checks its own work.

KEYWORD: "FEW-SHOT"
Provide examples for AI to follow.

OTHER META KEYWORDS:
"One-Liner" - Solve in single line of code
"Glossary" - Generate definitions of terms in code
"Annotate" - Add line-by-line explanations


================================================================================
SECTION 14: QUICK REFERENCE CHEAT SHEETS
================================================================================

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
14.1 BEFORE SENDING ANY PROMPT, CHECK:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[ ] Did I use tags/delimiters to separate sections?
[ ] Did I specify exact numbers (word count, bullet count)?
[ ] Did I define the output format (JSON, table, list)?
[ ] Did I write in the tone I want back?
[ ] Did I proofread for typos?
[ ] Did I say what TO do (not what NOT to do)?
[ ] Did I specify the audience?


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
14.2 KEYWORDS BY DEVELOPMENT PHASE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

PHASE 1: SETUP & PLANNING
KEYWORD           | WHAT IT DOES
------------------|--------------------------------
"Act as..."       | Sets the persona/expertise
"Scaffold"        | Creates files/folders
"Skeleton"        | Basic code structure
"Design Pattern"  | Forces standard structures
"Microservices"   | Distributed architecture
"Mock"            | Fake data for planning

PHASE 2: CODING
KEYWORD           | WHAT IT DOES
------------------|--------------------------------
"Idiomatic"       | Uses native language features
"Modular"         | Small, reusable pieces
"Standard Library"| No external packages
"Functional"      | Pure functions/immutability
"Type-safe"       | Prevents type errors
"Modern"          | Latest syntax

PHASE 3: DATA & LOGIC
KEYWORD           | WHAT IT DOES
------------------|--------------------------------
"Upsert"          | Update if exists, else insert
"Idempotent"      | Safe to run multiple times
"Atomic"          | All-or-nothing transactions
"Recursive"       | Function calls itself
"Memoization"     | Cache results for speed
"ETL"             | Extract, Transform, Load

PHASE 4: SECURITY & QUALITY
KEYWORD           | WHAT IT DOES
------------------|--------------------------------
"Sanitize"        | Clean inputs to stop hacks
"OWASP Top 10"    | Check common vulnerabilities
"Edge Cases"      | Handle weird scenarios
"Production-ready"| Add logging/error handling
"Robust"          | Doesn't crash easily
"Circuit Breaker" | Stop calling broken services

PHASE 5: DEBUGGING & EXPLANATION
KEYWORD           | WHAT IT DOES
------------------|--------------------------------
"Root Cause"      | Find WHY it broke
"Dry Run"         | Step through code mentally
"ELI5"            | Explain simply
"Annotate"        | Add explanatory comments
"Visualize"       | Draw diagrams
"Step by step"    | Chain-of-thought reasoning


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
14.3 ALL KEYWORDS BY CATEGORY
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CATEGORY            | TOP KEYWORDS
--------------------|----------------------------------------------------------
Structure           | Scaffold, Modular, Clean Architecture, SOLID
Quality             | Idiomatic, Production-ready, Robust, Type-safe
Safety              | Idempotent, Atomic, Sanitize, Least Privilege
Performance         | Lazy Loading, Memoization, N+1, Batch Processing
